    "created_at": "2023-05-23T16:22:09Z",
    "updated_at": "2023-05-23T16:22:37Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I've been able to resolve this by doing the following:\r\n1. Add 'timeout' param to the RPC call.  Example:\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\", \"method\":\"^Cbug_traceTransaction\", \"params\":[\"0xa97067dd04cf7ab72a11c56af7506e16b0b70a6b0131840c7221e1aad05ba753\", {\"timeout\":\"120s\", \"tracer\": \"callTracer\"}], \"id\":1}\r\n\r\n2. Configure the node to have extended read and idle timeouts:\r\n- create a directory (e.g. configs) and create a file called l2geth.toml that has the following:\r\n_[Node.HTTPTimeouts]\r\nReadTimeout = 120000000000\r\nWriteTimeout = 30000000000\r\nIdleTimeout = 120000000000_\r\n\r\n- modify the docker-compose.yml to mount the directory as a volume called /configs/\r\n- modify the l2geth-start.sh script to have a new option called --configs=/configs/l2geth.toml",
